:::summary
*The Hobbit, or There and Back Again* (1937) is J.R.R. Tolkien's beloved adventure story following Bilbo Baggins, a comfort-loving hobbit, who is swept up by the wizard Gandalf and thirteen dwarves on a quest to reclaim a mountain kingdom from the dragon Smaug. At once a children's tale and a work of deep mythological imagination, *The Hobbit* introduced the world to Middle-earth and laid the groundwork for *The Lord of the Rings*. It remains one of the best-selling and most beloved novels ever written.
:::

